div.p:
What will it profit us to heare and read,
•• at ſorrow and ſighing ſhall flye away, and that tears ſhall be wiped from the eyes of his, and 〈◊〉 there ſhall be no more ſorrow nor paine;
•• ereas thou and I have (it may be) neither •• tience to wait, nor faith to beleeve our 〈◊〉 intereſt in theſe things?
